29/03/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Federal Human Rights Minister Rasim Ljajic confirmed on Tuesday (29 March) that war crimes indictee Sreten Lukic underwent successful surgery at the Clinical Centre of Serbia earlier in the day. The procedure was initially planned for Monday. Ljajic said the retired Serbian police general would be recovering under doctors' supervision. He did not comment on the possible date of Lukic's departure for The Hague.
Also Tuesday, Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic wraps up a trip to Algiers, where he and Algerian counterpart Abdelaziz Belkhadem agreed to boost bilateral relations, particularly business ties. (Beta, RTRS - 29/03/05; B92, Beta, Tanjug - 28/03/05)
